      "type": "ambiguity",
      "description": "The partner API backward-compatibility strategy is unspecified. External partners currently receive single-recipient payloads. The requirement does not define how multi-recipient shipments should be represented to partners who haven't upgraded — send only a primary recipient? Reject? Send multiple payloads?",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["External Partners", "Operations"],
      "options": [
        "API versioning: v1 continues to send single-recipient format (primary recipient only), v2 sends full multi-recipient payload",
        "Expand the existing payload with a recipients array while keeping the legacy recipient field populated for backward compat",
        "Require all partners to upgrade before multi-recipient shipments go live"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Option 2 — additive expansion. Keep the legacy single-recipient field populated (with the first/primary recipient) and add a recipients array. This is non-breaking for existing integrations while enabling new ones."
